      <h2>How to play <strong>ApplesToo</strong></h2>
      <span class="byline">
        There are two decks of cards: Things, which are red, and Descriptions, which are green. During any given round, each player has seven red cards. Each round, there is one player who is  the "chooser". This player selects the top card from the green deck and displays it to the other players. The other players pick from the red cards they have and click the one which they think best represents, or relates to the green card of the round. The "chooser" in the round does not submit any of their red cards. After all other players have submitted their cards, the "chooser" will reveal all submitted cards and choose the card they like best. The player who submitted the chosen card will get one point. The first player to reach 5 points wins.
